quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  35,45,"If God were to punish people ˹immediately˺ for what they have committed, He would not have left a single living being on earth. But He delays them for an appointed term. And when their time arrives, then surely God is All-Seeing of His servants"
  36,1,Yâ-Sĩn
  36,2,"By the Quran, rich in wisdom"
  36,3,You ˹O Prophet˺ are truly one of the messengers
  36,4,upon the Straight Path
  36,5,"˹This is˺ a revelation from the Almighty, Most Merciful"
  36,6,"so that you may warn a people whose forefathers were not warned, and so are heedless"
  36,7,"The decree ˹of torment˺ has already been justified against most of them, for they will never believe"
  36,8,"˹It is as if˺ We have put shackles around their necks up to their chins, so their heads are forced up"
  36,9,"and have placed a barrier before them and a barrier behind them and covered them ˹all˺ up, so they fail to see ˹the truth˺"
  36,10,It is the same whether you warn them or not—they will never believe
  36,11,You can only warn those who follow the Reminder and are in awe of the Most Compassionate without seeing Him. So give them good news of forgiveness and an honourable reward
  36,12,"It is certainly We Who resurrect the dead, and write what they send forth and what they leave behind. Everything is listed by Us in a perfect Record"